@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}

<main>
    <section class="row" aria-labelledby="aspnetTitle">
        <h1 id="title">Farm Management</h1>
        <p class="lead">Welcome back to the Pumpkin Patch! .</p>
        <p class="lead">Thank you for using the most efficiant way to organize your crops, supplies, equipment, and more!</p>
        <p><a href="https://wloy12345.github.io/" class="btn btn-primary btn-md">Visit our website &raquo;</a></p>
        &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
        
    </section>

    <div class="row">
        <section class="col-md-4" aria-labelledby="gettingStartedTitle">
            <h2 id="gettingStartedTitle">My Crops</h2>

            <style>
                section.col-md-4 {
                    border-radius: 25px;
                    border: 2px solid #73AD21;
                    padding: 20px;
                    width: 500px;
                    height: auto;
                }
            </style>


            <img src="~/Images/corn.jpg" width="200"/>
            <p>
                Pumpkin Patch gives you an easy to use index to organize the crops that you grow (or plan to grow) on your farm. Whether you grow 5 or 500 crops, let Pumpkin Patch do the work for you so you don't have to.
            <p> <a href=" @Url.Action("Index", "CROPs", new { area = "Crops", controller = "CROPs" })" class="btn btn-success"> Go to My Crops &raquo; </a></p>
        </section>
        &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;

        <section class="col-md-4" aria-labelledby="librariesTitle">
            <h2 id="librariesTitle">My Supplies</h2>
            
            <img src="~/Images/haybale.jpg"  width="200"/>
            <p>Organize the supplies you have on hand so you know what you have and when you are running low. With Pumpkin Patch you can filter by the type of supply for easier viewing.</p>
            <p> <a href=" @Url.Action("Index", "SUPPLies", new { area = "Supplies", controller = "SUPPLies" })" class="btn btn-success"> Go to My Supplies &raquo; </a></p>
        </section>
        &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;
        <p>

        </p>
        <section class="col-md-4" aria-labelledby="hostingTitle">
            <h2 id="hostingTitle">Equipment</h2>
            
            <img src="~/Images/tractor.jpg"  width="200" />
            <p>Keep an inventory of what equipment is in stock and ready to use. Keep a schedule of what equipment is in use and when. </p>
            <p>
                <a href=" @Url.Action("Index", "EQUIPMENTs", new { area = "Equipment", controller = "EQUIPMENTs" })" class="btn btn-success"> Go to My Equipment &raquo; </a>
            </p>


        </section>
       
        &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;


        <section class="col-md-4" aria-labelledby="hostingTitle">
            <h2 id="hostingTitle">Customers</h2>
           
            <img src="~/Images/customers-shopping.jpeg"  width="200"/>
            <p>Reach out to your loyal customers at the click of a button to let them know what products you have available and where they will be sold!</p>
            <p><a href=" @Url.Action("Index", "CUSTOMERs", new { area = "Customers", controller = "CUSTOMERs" })" class="btn btn-success"> Go to My Customers &raquo; </a></p>
        </section>

    </div>
</main>